data.text:
Frances Williams Duke, 83, of 2101 Rolesville Rd., Wake Forest, 27587 passed away at the home of her daughter in Aiken, SC on August 15, 2017. Frances was born October 10, 1933 in Franklin County to the late William N. Williams and Margaret Braswell Williams. After high school graduation, she worked 13 years with the DMV and 21 years with the NC Automobile Dealers Association. She was a member of Bethany Baptist Church. Frances was very devoted to her family, especially her grandchildren.

Funeral service 2:30 pm, Saturday, August 19, 2017 at Bethany Baptist Church, 3417 Rolesville Rd, Wendell, 27591. Burial will follow in the church cemetery.

The family will receive relatives and friends prior to the service from 1:00 to 2:30 pm at the church.

Surviving: daughter, Lisa Duke Rezac and her husband Mitchell James Rezac of Aiken, SC; her beloved grandchildren: Robert Lawrence Rezac, Bethany Gale Rezac; sister, Shelby W. Senter of Youngsville.

In addition to her parents, Frances was preceded in death by her husband, Bennie Lawrence Duke; brother, William Williams, Jr.; sisters: Alma Booth and Marie Bonner.

Flowers are accepted or memorial contributions may be made to MSA Home Health & Hospice 186 Fabian Dr. Aiken, SC 29803.
